<p><font size="4" face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">IC Cards continued:</font></p>
<p align="center"><font size="4" face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><img src="images/handheld_ic_card.jpg" width="469" height="268"></font></p>
<p align="center"><font size="4" face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><img src="images/handheld_ic_card2.jpg" width="469" height="268"></font></p>
<p><font size="4" face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">The handheld IC is used 
  to format the data for handheld devices. The handheld IC sends data request 
  messages to the crossing and track ICs.</font></p>
<p align="center"><img src="images/vehicle_ic_card.jpg" width="469" height="268"></p>
<p align="center"><img src="images/vehicle_ic_card2.jpg" width="469" height="268"></p>
<p><font size="4" face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">The vehicle IC has a similar 
  purpose to that of the handheld IC, but of course it is designed to provide 
  data formatted for a device mounted in a vehicle.</font></p>
